Class FriendsList

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<Friend>, java.util.Collection<Friend>, java.util.List<Friend>, java.util.RandomAccess
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TrackedFriendsList

    public class FriendsList
extends java.util.ArrayList<Friend>
implements Observable
    An ArrayList of all the Friends the user has. This list includes all tracked and untracked friends. Friends are ordered in the arraylist by the order in which the user added them as friends (first-added appears first in the list). In addition to the basic functionality of ArrayLists, FriendsLists can be searched by the friend's email address. Additionally, the ArrayList's add function is overridden so that the same Friend cannot be added to the current user's FriendsList multiple times.

    The current user's FriendsList can be viewed, and new friends can be added to it, in the FriendsListActivity. A friend can be removed from the current user's FriendsList by deleting the friend in the FriendsProfileActivity.

    • Constructor Detail

      • FriendsList

        public FriendsList()
        Default constructor used when the current user logs in for the first time (thereby creating their account). A user begins with no friends, so an empty FriendsList is instantiated using the default ArrayList constructor.

      • FriendsList

        public FriendsList(java.util.Collection<? extends Friend> c)
        Constructor for instantiating the FriendsList of an existing user. Constructs a FriendsList from an arbitrary Collection of Friends using the equivalent ArrayList constructor. The given collection can be empty.

        This constructor should be called when a user with an existing account logs in. The FriendsList is instantiated with the user's previous FriendsList data. This data is retrieved from the Elastic Search server if the device is online, or from the user's local phone storage if it is offline. If the user has no friends, this constructor will still be called with an empty collection.

        Parameters:
        c - a Collection of Friend objects; a list of the user's Friends

        Parameters:

      • getFriendByUsername

        public Friend getFriendByUsername(java.lang.String username)
        Searches for a Friend in the FriendsList using the specified username (the friends email address). Returns the Friend object if a friend with that email address is found in the FriendsList; otherwise, returns null. This method is called to retrieve the Friend when the current user requests details about them, for example it is used in FriendsInventoryActivity to retrieve the inventory of the Friend the current user is viewing in the FriendsProfileActivity.
        Parameters:
        username - - the username of the friend to be searched
        Returns:
        Friend - the Friend with the specified username if found; otherwise, null

      • getFriendIndexByUsername

        public java.lang.Integer getFriendIndexByUsername(java.lang.String username)
        Searches for the index of the Friend in the FriendsList using the specified username (the friend's email address). Returns the index of the Friend with that email address in the FriendsList if a Friend with that email address is found in the FriendsList; otherwise, returns null. Friends are ordered int the FriendsList in the order they are added, with the Friend that is added first at index 0.
        Parameters:
        username - - the username of the friend to be searched
        Returns:
        Integer - the index in the FriendsList of the Friend with the specified email address if found; otherwise, null

      • add

        public boolean add(Friend friend)
        Add a new friend to FriendsList. The method returns a Boolean to indicate if the friend was successfully added to the list or not. If the friend was successfully added then add returns True. If not add returns False. The most likely reason for add to fail is if the user tries to add a friend that is already in their FriendsList. Duplicates friends are not permitted, so if the friend being added to the current user's FriendsList is already in their FriendsList then that Friend will not be added again and add will return False.

        This method is invoked by the FriendsListController after a user tries to add a new Friend from the FriendsListActivity.
